Elegance Reimagined at
Karma Château de Samary

Perched just above the medieval splendour of Carcassonne, Karma Château de Samary is a harmonious balance between aristocratic grandeur and contemporary warmth. Here, exquisite chandeliers, patterned wallpapers and high-ceilinged rooms tell tales of la belle époque.

Outside, manicured gardens, garden games, a private pool and a scattering of bicycles invite languid exploration, while the air itself seems to hum with history and honeyed light.

Winter Wonders Beyond the Château

Step beyond the château and discover the quiet magic of southern France. Wander through olive groves and artisan villages, taste local wines and olive oils, and feel the region’s timeless charm come alive

In winter, Carcassonne glows with festive lights and Christmas markets, Toulouse charms with riverside stalls and pink façades, and Montpellier buzzes with café life by the sea, each just a short journey away.

A Timeless Winter Escape

Back at Karma Château de Samary, expect an intimate, indulgent and distinctly French festive feeling to continue. From its continental breakfasts to cosy evenings spent savouring local wines, every timeless moment is tailored for beauty, not bustle.

So, let your winter unwrap like a romance novel this
winter and wrap yourself in the quintessential spirit of
southern France.
